abstract: As each leading piano manufacturer aims to give the instruments of his manufacture special qualities and excellencies which shall distinguish them from all others, the Weber pianos have peculiarities which are not to be found in any other instruments. The chief of these, Mr. Weber claims, is the great "singing" power of the strings, a power gamed by lengthening the strings beyond the usual measure.

abstract: A recent arrival at this port reports that an abandoned bark, loaded with Oregon pine, was picked up near Manzanilla, west coast of Mexico. Her name is supposed to be the Midas. This may be the vessel referred to.
